This paper discusses the need for threat modeling in data analysis processes, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of considering socio-technical systems, which falls under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for organizational and legal mitigations, which could fall under the sub-categories of cyber law (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of technology in decision-making processes, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
